FBIS3-7867 "dreeu040_c_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC Foreign Ministry `Shaken' by Hebron Massacre LD2802183694 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 GMT 28 Feb 94 LD2802183694 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Language: Czech Article Type:BFN [Text] The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Czech Republic was shaken by the report on the horrific massacre of Palestinian Muslims in Hebron in Israel, says the statement released today by Vit Kurfirst, the ministry's press spokesman . The ministry emphasizes that it is up to all those who participate in the conflict and up to the whole international community to prevent this tragic development from leading to further escalation of tension and from becoming an insurmountable obstacle to the promising developments in the peace talks so far. The statement voices a hope that all of the involved sides will exercise full responsibility for the lives of other people and will begin speedy and effective talks aimed at a just, lasting, and comprehensive peaceful solution.
